webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Torpa Church is one of the more noticeable medieval churches in Östergötland. Performed in stone around 1460, it replaced a former church building of timber. Preserved timber from this 1200th century church is provided with paintings attributed to the so-called Rising Master. The present exterior received the church when it was built with cross arms in a south-north direction in 1674. The belfry is considered to be built in 1666 - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000292. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419838. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
